snippet.textDisplay:
Olivia Hye and the Diverging Timelines of the Loonaverse: Connecting love4eva, Egoist, Hi High, Butterfly, and So What

Olivia Hye is a special girl in the Loonaverse. She's the last and therefore, newest, most improved creation in the Loonaverse. Her color is even silver, which is not like any other girl in the group. A metallic shade, and is therefore, reflective of light just like the moon. Therefore, Olivia Hye is the girl that contains all the Loonas because she absorbs and reflect white light. This means that all of the memories, mistakes, powers, and achievements of the other members, are in her. Ultimately, this means that her actions in the Loonaverse reflects what happens to a timeline and all of the girls. One only has to look in her in past videos to see that she was dressed like Yves, dancing in a dark parking lot like Choerry, splayed on a bed like YeoJin, teleporting like JinSoul, etc. This is actually backed by a popular theory on "one," a yyxy launch teaser.

In love4eva, it seems confusing as to whether Olivia stayed in Eden. The answer? She did. And she didn't. These choices launched a Butterfly effect. One only has to look at the choreography of "#" and she'd that her shoulder roll spreads towards the other girls behind her--she starts the small change, but it spreads to the whole Loonaverse. Her confusion split and made branch timelines in the Loonaverse as she explored different possibilities. This is why she also sings I'm Hi High, "Been Been There, Never Been Been there." She was both in Eden and wasn't. Both of her choices, depending on who you ask, could be good or bad, and both are risky.

In Hi High, she took a leap of faith and stayed in Eden. She was peering down at Yves, the girl from the "one" teaser who represents Faith. She jumped, and below are Love (Chuu) and Hope (Go Won), wearing white dresses, pure and untarnished creations who were playing on Yellow swings and playing with Yellow smoke. I think that Eden has a Yellow pallete because it is the color of the original Adam--Hyun Jin, the first girl that the Loonaverse Godess Heejin created. This is why all of the golf balls in ViViD came out yellow. With Adam (HyunJin) being the rightful steward of Eden, it only follows that the girls are dressed in Yellow uniforms. However, this staying caused a conflict in Olivia's mind. New human that she was, she still is human. And that's when the rumination (deep thinking that comes from wisdom, a color that is usually associated with blue, aka JinSoul) and passion (usually associated with red or Kim Lip) came in.

Wisdom and passion, by themselves, are ambiguous. Again, depending on who you ask. One person can be so wise as to take a step back and be more logical, or use those brains to outsmart others with guile and cunning. Passion is good because it makes you love people and what you do. But there are also crimes of passion.

This is why Hi High is a loop. It is the "good" choice. They preserve that "good time line" of staying in Eden by running really fast, and rewinding everything. One of the paradoxes of time travel, is that for one to go back to the past, one must travel faster than the speed of light. This is why Kim Lip running is a crucial piece of imagery in Hi High. She guards that timeline with her super speed along with the help of other girls. She is also launched a Butterfly effect on that timeline.

But as JinSoul raps in Egoist, "for the sin of swallowing you, you become more beautiful." And why Olivia has blue highlights in her hair in Butterfly, and she sings, "All I see around me is blue." Having been granted free will, she feels something lacking in the seemingly happy Hi High timeline. She ruminated so much that Faith, Hope, and Love abandoned her. In the "one" teaser, Olivia was Anger, the free spirit repressed by the strict rules of Eden. She was applauded by HeeJin, the headmistress of the yyxy school (In ViViD, HeeJin was wearing a black dress seated on a chair). But Olivia's face was hidden by a shadow. This is why love4eva also cuts to a scene where Olivia got out of the castle and into the dark forest. In a different timeline, she left Eden. This led to the events of Egoist, and eventually, So What.

Self-Love depending on which perception, is also ambiguous. The person who tirelessly gives themselves to others needs a break--and making sure that their own needs are addressed isn't a bad thing. But to others, this may seem selfish, indulgent, or entitled. This is why So What echoes the question asked by the yyxy girls: Is it bad to disobey God? Or is it much worse to be passive about one's own fate? The Girls repeatedly sing "I'm so Bad." But truly, what is Bad? And how is one person Free, exactly?

Anger isn't also bad. It is actually our body's response to stressful situations because it gives us energy to effect change in our lives. It's how we express that Anger that could have good or bad effects.

Olivia thought that by burning down the Loonaverse, she would be free. But is she? The feather in the end caught fire, but was restored to its unscathed state. By aiming to be free, ironically, Olivia imprisoned herself in another time loop--one that aims to preserve the choice where she feels free. Her wisdom and rumination colored the sky behind her (Blue) and her passion lit her (Red) and fueled her actions. Again she travelled faster than the speed of light (which is why Kim Lip is very much seen in the So What video, and why her color has dominated the set) to preserve the Freedom timeline.
